  "text": "An interesting recent paper [CITATION_1] derived the generalised tangent space required for the closure of the generalised diffeomorphisms associated with U duality. They found a hierarchy of tensor coordinates which were those found in papers on E 11 . However, unlike some other recent works, reference [CITATION_2] did not borrow the tangent space structures from E 11 papers but derived them from a different perspective. The generalised tangent space encoded in the E 11 ⊗ s l 1 non-linear realisation arises in a simple way from the l 1 realisation and it is the agreement with this that has been found in reference [CITATION_3] . The results contained in [CITATION_4] are also consistent with the approach of this paper that takes the gauge parameters to belong to the l 1 representation. It would be interesting to make detailed contact between this paper, reference [CITATION_5] and other recent papers that consider local transformations associated with U duality.",
